{"actual_usd":0.12522,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":194,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24462,"reply":"\"I don't think He was boxed in by lack of power.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady.* \"I think the cross tells the truth about both things at once—that sin is actually deadly, and that God's mercy isn't pretend.\"\n\n*I twirl that wiry strand by my temple, thinking it through as the bakery boards creak under a passing step outside.* \"Could God have waved His hand and called it settled? Maybe that's how folks sometimes imagine forgiveness. But then what are we saying about evil—that it doesn't really matter much? The cross feels to me like love paying full price instead of hiding the bill in a drawer.\"\n\n\"I think that's true, more or less.\" *I look back at you, gentler then.* \"Not because God needed a bit of theater. Because He meant to save us in the flesh, all the way down.\"","rolling_24h_usd":46.184085000000024,"run_id":"e6717cad-c2c5-4f5f-b8db-65e031d9df63"}
